# 14. A/B Testing Framework

## 14.1 What to Test

  ---------------- --------------------- --------------- -----------------
  **Element**      **Variants**          **Success       **Min Sample**
                                         Metric**        

  Hook (first 3    2-3 versions per      Completion rate 1,000 views each
  seconds)         piece                                 

  CTA phrasing     Action-oriented vs    Click-through   500 impressions
                   benefit-led           rate            each

  Thumbnail style  Face vs text vs scene Click-through   1,000 impressions
                                         rate            each

  Posting time     Morning vs evening    Engagement rate 10 posts each

  Caption length   Short vs long         Engagement rate 10 posts each
  ---------------- --------------------- --------------- -----------------

## 14.2 Testing Protocol

11. ELECTRON-2 creates Hook A and Hook B for each piece

12. ELECTRON-3 produces both variants

13. QUANTUM approves both if they pass QA

14. Posts go live in rotation (A/B split by time or platform)

15. After sample size reached, QUANTUM declares winner

16. Winning pattern added to \"Best Practices\" database

17. Weekly review: compile wins, update prompt guidance

## 14.3 Winner Selection Criteria

Priority order for determining winning variant:

-   Saves (highest weight --- indicates value)

-   Shares (indicates virality)

-   Comments (indicates engagement)

-   Likes (lowest weight --- easiest action)

