# 16. Audit Trail & Compliance

## 16.1 What Gets Logged

  ----------------- ---------------------------------- --------------------
  **Event**         **Data Captured**                  **Retention**

  Trend discovery   Source, timestamp, risk            90 days
                    assessment, agent version          

  Content creation  All drafts, revisions, approval    1 year
                    decisions, reasons                 

  QA decisions      Checklist results, pass/fail,      1 year
                    reviewer (agent)                   

  Publishing        Full metadata (see Section 12.2)   2 years

  Edits/Deletions   What changed, why, who authorized  2 years

  System events     Errors, restarts, config changes   90 days
  ----------------- ---------------------------------- --------------------

## 16.2 Compliance Requirements

-   All health-related content must be traceable to source research

-   Subscription marketing must comply with FTC guidelines

-   GDPR: No personal data in content without consent

-   Platform ToS: Content must comply with each platform\'s policies

-   Audit export: Ability to export full history for legal review

## 16.3 Content Versioning

Every piece of content has a version history:

-   v0.1 --- Initial draft from ELECTRON-2

-   v0.2 --- Revision after QUANTUM feedback

-   v1.0 --- Approved for production

-   v1.0-rendered --- Final asset from ELECTRON-3

-   v1.0-published --- Posted version with platform confirmation

# 17. Escalation Matrix

## 17.1 Decision Escalation

  --------------------- ----------- ------------------ ----------- --------------
  **Scenario**          **Initial   **Escalate To**    **SLA**     **Action**
                        Handler**                                  

  Health claim in       QUANTUM     Human Review Queue 1 hour      Pause
  approved content                                                 publishing,
                                                                   manual review

  Legal gray area       QUANTUM     Legal/Compliance   4 hours     Hold until
  (claims)                                                         cleared

  Brand crisis          QUANTUM     Leadership         Immediate   Pause all
  (negative PR)                                                    publishing

  Technical failure     E3          Infrastructure +   15 min      Switch to
  (API down)                        Backup Tool                    backup

  QUANTUM agent failure System      Human Operator     30 min      Manual
                        Monitor                                    approval mode

  Content already       Anyone      Crisis Protocol    Immediate   Delete +
  published with issue                                             document
  --------------------- ----------- ------------------ ----------- --------------

## 17.2 Human Override Protocol

Humans can intervene at any point:

18. Access override console (requires authentication)

19. Issue HOLD command to pause all publishing

20. Review flagged content manually

21. Issue OVERRIDE-APPROVE or OVERRIDE-BLOCK

22. Document reason in audit log

23. Issue RESUME command when resolved

# 18. Failure Modes & Recovery Playbook

## 18.1 Common Failures

  ------------------ --------------- --------------- ---------------------
  **Failure**        **Symptom**     **Root Cause**  **Recovery**

  Trend contains     QUANTUM blocks  E1 missed risk  Replace with safe
  medical claims                                     alternative

  Script has banned  QUANTUM blocks  E2 prompt drift Return with fix
  phrases                                            notes, update prompt

  Video render       QA fails        Wrong export    Re-export with
  quality poor                       settings        correct preset

  Broken link in CTA Link check      URL changed     Update link,
                     fails                           re-verify

  API rate limit hit Errors in logs  Too many        Implement backoff,
                                     requests        queue jobs

  Laptop restart     Pipeline stops  Power/OS issue  Auto-resume from
                                                     checkpoint,
                                                     re-approve pending
  ------------------ --------------- --------------- ---------------------

## 18.2 Recovery Protocol

24. DETECT: Monitoring alerts or agent reports failure

25. PAUSE: If any risk of bad publish, stop publishing queue

26. DIAGNOSE: Identify root cause from logs

27. FIX: Apply correction (re-run job, update config, fix content)

28. VERIFY: Confirm fix resolved issue

29. DOCUMENT: Record in incident log with learnings

30. PREVENT: Update rules/prompts to prevent recurrence

31. RESUME: Return to normal operations

## 18.3 Incident Severity Classification

  -------------- ---------------------- ------------------ -----------------
  **Severity**   **Definition**         **Example**        **Response**

  SEV-1          Policy violation       Medical claim in   Immediate delete,
                 published to public    live post          crisis review

  SEV-2          Pipeline completely    n8n crashed, no    All-hands, manual
                 down                   recovery           mode

  SEV-3          Quality degradation    30% QA fail rate   Pause non-urgent,
                                                           investigate

  SEV-4          Minor issue            One failed export  Fix and continue
  -------------- ---------------------- ------------------ -----------------

